item.title: Help me please
item.dc:creator: @Epic_Ancient Epic Ancient
item.description:
@Epic_Ancient wrote:

[quote=“hokabo, post:1, topic:301025”]ok heres the problem. I am making my own server i downloaded project fubergen as my client and am using testscape as my source. i also am using no-ip. Two problems here. 1st of all i dont really know how to use my source with my client considering it looks the same and people just open up both or something im not really sure. 2nd of all when i try to ping my no-ip server it sais it has a ping of 3ms. but when i try to log in i get an error that sais…“Unexpected server response please try using a different world”. i am open to any comments on these two questions thank you for your time.

-hokabo[/quote]

Regrammarization for the people who would say “what?” or “explain better”:

Okay, here’s the problem. I am making my own server. I downloaded Project Fubergen as my client to use, and I’m using Testscape for my source.
I’m also using no-ip. (You shouldn’t have to unless you port forwarded.)
There’s two problems:

  1. I don’t really know how to use my source with the client, considering it looks the same, and people just open up both or something; I’m not really sure.
  2. When I try to ping my no-ip, it says my server has a ping of 3miliseconds. When I try to log in I get an error that says: “Unexpected Server Response, Please Try using a Different World.”

I am open to any comments on these two problems. Thank you for your time.

  1. Make sure your client is connecting to IP: 127.0.0.1. Check this in GUI.java, or EGUI.java, in your client folder. Then try and run your server, then run your client.
    (You DON’T need No-ip for your server if you’re connecting to 127.0.0.1 - Localhost. You only need No-ip if you port forwarded and want people on your server.)
  2. No-ip part, you don’t need. Fix #1 and #2 should be automatically fixed.
